  "question": "Congestion Control",
  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html>\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<title>Congestion Control Interactive Simulator</title>\n<style>\n  /* Extremely minimal visual design: plain black text on white background */\n  html,body { margin:12px; padding:0; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; color:black; background:white; }\n  h1 { font-size:18px; margin:6px 0; }\n  p { margin:6px 0; font-size:13px; }\n  .row { display:block; margin:8px 0; }\n  label { display:inline-block; font-size:13px; width:160px; vertical-align:top; }\n  input, select, button, textarea { font-size:12px; margin:2px 0; }\n  fieldset { margin-bottom:10px; padding:8px; }\n  canvas { border:1px solid #000; display:block; margin:6px 0; }\n  .controls { max-width:980px; }\n  .small { font-size:12px; }\n  .log { width:98%; height:120px; font-family: monospace; font-size:12px; }\n  .inline { display:inline-block; margin-right:8px; }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h1>Congestion Control Interactive Simulator</h1>\n<p>This simulator models sender congestion-control behavior (Reno, AIMD, simplified CUBIC, simplified BBR) with interactive controls, manual events, scenario save/load, and plotting. Use the controls below to explore many paths: change network parameters while running, inject losses/delays, switch algorithms, and step through time.</p>\n\n<div class=\"controls\">\n\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Algorithm & Core Parameters</legend>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <label for=\"algo\">Algorithm</label>\n      <select id=\"algo\">\n        <option value=\"reno\">TCP Reno (slow start / avoidance / fast retransmit)</option>\n        <option value=\"aimd\">AIMD (custom)</option>\n        <option value=\"cubic\">CUBIC (simplified)</option>\n        <option value=\"bbr\">BBR (simplified)</option>\n      </select>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <label for=\"initCWND\">Initial cwnd (pkts)</label>\n      <input id=\"initCWND\" type=\"number\" value=\"2\" min=\"1\" step=\"1\" />\n      <label style=\"width:120px;\">Initial ssthresh</label>\n      <input id=\"initSSTH\" type=\"number\" value=\"1000\" min=\"1\" step=\"1\" />\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <label for=\"mss\">MSS (bytes)</label>\n      <input id=\"mss\" type=\"number\" value=\"1460\" min=\"100\" step=\"1\" />\n      <label style=\"width:120px;\">DupACKs threshold</label>\n      <input id=\"dupThresh\" type=\"number\" value=\"3\" min=\"1\" step=\"1\" />\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\" id=\"aimdParams\" >\n      <label for=\"ai\">AIMD: additive increase / RTT</label>\n      <input id=\"ai\" type=\"number\" value=\"1\" min=\"0\" step=\"0.1\" />\n      <label style=\"width:120px;\">mult. decrease (beta)</label>\n      <input id=\"beta\" type=\"number\" value=\"0.5\" min=\"0\" max=\"1\" step=\"0.01\" />\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\" id=\"cubicParams\" style=\"display:none;\">\n      <label for=\"cubicC\">CUBIC: C value</label>\n      <input id=\"cubicC\" type=\"number\" value=\"0.4\" min=\"0\" step=\"0.01\" />\n      <label style=\"width:120px;\">TCP-friendly factor</label>\n      <input id=\"tcpFriend\" type=\"number\" value=\"0.7\" min=\"0\" step=\"0.01\" />\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\" id=\"bbrParams\" style=\"display:none;\">\n      <label for=\"bbrGain\">BBR: cwnd gain</label>\n      <input id=\"bbrGain\" type=\"number\" value=\"2\" min=\"0.1\" step=\"0.1\" />\n      <label style=\"width:120px;\">ProbeBW interval (s)</label>\n      <input id=\"bbrInterval\" type=\"number\" value=\"1\" min=\"0.1\" step=\"0.1\" />\n    </div>\n  </fieldset>\n\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Network & Link Parameters</legend>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <label for=\"rtt\">Base RTT (ms)</label>\n      <input id=\"rtt\" type=\"number\" value=\"80\" min=\"1\" step=\"1\" />\n      <label style=\"width:120px;\">Bandwidth (Mbps)</label>\n      <input id=\"bandwidth\" type=\"number\" value=\"10\" min=\"0.1\" step=\"0.1\" />\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <label for=\"queue\">Queue size (packets)</label>\n      <input id=\"queue\" type=\"number\" value=\"100\" min=\"1\" step=\"1\" />\n      <label style=\"width:120px;\">Cross-traffic (Mbps)</label>\n      <input id=\"xtraffic\" type=\"number\" value=\"0\" min=\"0\" step=\"0.1\" />\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <label for=\"lossModel\">Loss model</label>\n      <select id=\"lossModel\">\n        <option value=\"queue\">Queue overflow only</option>\n        <option value=\"random\">Random loss (probability)</option>\n        <option value=\"none\">No spontaneous loss</option>\n      </select>\n      <label style=\"width:120px;\">Random loss p</label>\n      <input id=\"lossProb\" type=\"number\" value=\"0.001\" min=\"0\" max=\"1\" step=\"0.0001\" />\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <label for=\"mode\">Simulation granularity</label>\n      <select id=\"mode\">\n        <option value=\"packet\">Per-packet discrete</option>\n        <option value=\"rtt\">Per-RTT aggregated</option>\n      </select>\n      <label style=\"width:120px;\">Tick ms</label>\n      <input id=\"tickMs\" type=\"number\" value=\"10\" min=\"1\" step=\"1\" />\n    </div>\n  </fieldset>\n\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Run Controls & Scheduling</legend>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <button id=\"playBtn\">Play</button>\n      <button id=\"stepBtn\">Step</button>\n      <button id=\"resetBtn\">Reset</button>\n      <button id=\"fastRunBtn\">Run 500 steps</button>\n      <label style=\"width:120px;\">Speed (steps/sec)</label>\n      <input id=\"speed\" type=\"number\" value=\"50\" min=\"1\" step=\"1\" />\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <label for=\"autoStopLoss\">Auto-stop on N losses (0=no)</label>\n      <input id=\"autoStopLoss\" type=\"number\" value=\"0\" min=\"0\" step=\"1\" />\n      <label style=\"width:120px;\">Record interval (ms)</label>\n      <input id=\"recordInt\" type=\"number\" value=\"100\" min=\"10\" step=\"10\" />\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <label for=\"simTime\">Sim time (s)</label>\n      <input id=\"simTime\" type=\"number\" value=\"0\" min=\"0\" step=\"1\" readonly />\n      <label style=\"width:120px;\">Events scheduled</label>\n      <input id=\"schedCount\" type=\"number\" value=\"0\" min=\"0\" step=\"1\" readonly />\n    </div>\n  </fieldset>\n\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Manual Events & Scenario</legend>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <label for=\"dropSeq\">Drop packet seq (manual)</label>\n      <input id=\"dropSeq\" type=\"number\" min=\"1\" step=\"1\" />\n      <button id=\"dropBtn\">Drop</button>\n\n      <label style=\"width:120px;\">Delay packet seq</label>\n      <input id=\"delaySeq\" type=\"number\" min=\"1\" step=\"1\" />\n      <label style=\"width:80px;\">ms</label>\n      <input id=\"delayMs\" type=\"number\" value=\"200\" min=\"1\" step=\"1\" style=\"width:80px;\" />\n      <button id=\"delayBtn\">Delay</button>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <label for=\"linkDownFor\">Take link down (ms)</label>\n      <input id=\"linkDownFor\" type=\"number\" value=\"0\" min=\"0\" step=\"10\" />\n      <button id=\"linkDownBtn\">Take Down</button>\n\n      <label style=\"width:120px;\">Inject cross traffic change</label>\n      <input id=\"setX\" type=\"number\" value=\"0\" min=\"0\" step=\"0.1\" />\n      <button id=\"setXBtn\">Set X-traffic</button>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <label for=\"saveScenario\">Save/Load Scenario</label>\n      <button id=\"saveBtn\">Save</button>\n      <button id=\"loadBtn\">Load</button>\n      <textarea id=\"scenarioJson\" rows=\"3\" cols=\"70\" placeholder=\"Scenario JSON appears here or paste to load\"></textarea>\n    </div>\n  </fieldset>\n\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Advanced Inspection</legend>\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <label for=\"showLog\">Show event log</label>\n      <input id=\"showLog\" type=\"checkbox\" checked />\n      <button id=\"clearLog\">Clear log</button>\n      <button id=\"exportLog\">Export log</button>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"row\">\n      <label for=\"inspectSeq\">Inspect packet seq</label>\n      <input id=\"inspectSeq\" type=\"number\" min=\"1\" step=\"1\" />\n      <button id=\"inspectBtn\">Inspect</button>\n      <label style=\"width:120px;\">Flight packets</label>\n      <input id=\"flightCount\" type=\"number\" value=\"0\" readonly />\n    </div>\n  </fieldset>\n\n</div>\n\n<fieldset>\n  <legend>Plots & Metrics</legend>\n  <canvas id=\"plot\" width=\"900\" height=\"200\"></canvas>\n  <div class=\"row\">\n    <label style=\"width:160px;\">Current cwnd</label><span id=\"cwndVal\">0</span>\n    <label style=\"width:120px;\">ssthresh</label><span id=\"ssthVal\">0</span>\n    <label style=\"width:120px;\">state</label><span id=\"stateVal\">-</span>\n    <label style=\"width:120px;\">RTT (ms)</label><span id=\"rttVal\">-</span>\n    <label style=\"width:120px;\">Throughput (Mbps)</label><span id=\"thrVal\">-</span>\n  </div>\n</fieldset>\n\n<fieldset>\n  <legend>Log</legend>\n  <textarea id=\"log\" class=\"log\"></textarea>\n</fieldset>\n\n<script>\n/*\n  Congestion Control Interactive Simulator\n  - Provides multiple algorithms: Reno, AIMD, simplified CUBIC, simplified BBR\n  - Packet-level (discrete) and RTT-aggregated modes\n  - Queue modeling with capacity, random loss, manual events\n  - Extensive controls for user-driven workflows: scheduling, manual packet drops/delays, link down, cross-traffic\n  - Plotting cwnd over time and metrics\n*/\n\n/* Simulation state and helpers */\n(function(){\n  // Utility\n  function nowMs(){ return sim.timeMs; }\n  function clamp(v,a,b){ return Math.max(a, Math.min(b, v)); }\n\n  // DOM\n  const dom = id => document.getElementById(id);\n\n  // Inputs\n  const algoEl = dom('algo');\n  const initCWND = dom('initCWND');\n  const initSSTH = dom('initSSTH');\n  const mssEl = dom('mss');\n  const dupThreshEl = dom('dupThresh');\n  const aiEl = dom('ai');\n  const betaEl = dom('beta');\n  const cubicC = dom('cubicC');\n  const tcpFriend = dom('tcpFriend');\n  const bbrGain = dom('bbrGain');\n  const bbrInterval = dom('bbrInterval');\n\n  const rttEl = dom('rtt');\n  const bandwidthEl = dom('bandwidth');\n  const queueEl = dom('queue');\n  const xtrafficEl = dom('xtraffic');\n  const lossModelEl = dom('lossModel');\n  const lossProbEl = dom('lossProb');\n  const modeEl = dom('mode');\n  const tickMsEl = dom('tickMs');\n\n  const playBtn = dom('playBtn');\n  const stepBtn = dom('stepBtn');\n  const resetBtn = dom('resetBtn');\n  const fastRunBtn = dom('fastRunBtn');\n  const speedEl = dom('speed');\n  const autoStopLoss = dom('autoStopLoss');\n  const recordInt = dom('recordInt');\n  const simTimeEl = dom('simTime');\n  const schedCountEl = dom('schedCount');\n\n  const dropSeqEl = dom('dropSeq');\n  const dropBtn = dom('dropBtn');\n  const delaySeqEl = dom('delaySeq');\n  const delayMsEl = dom('delayMs');\n  const delayBtn = dom('delayBtn');\n  const linkDownFor = dom('linkDownFor');\n  const linkDownBtn = dom('linkDownBtn');\n  const setX = dom('setX');\n  const setXBtn = dom('setXBtn');\n  const saveBtn = dom('saveBtn');\n  const loadBtn = dom('loadBtn');\n  const scenarioJson = dom('scenarioJson');\n\n  const showLog = dom('showLog');\n  const clearLogBtn = dom('clearLog');\n  const exportLogBtn = dom('exportLog');\n  const inspectSeq = dom('inspectSeq');\n  const inspectBtn = dom('inspectBtn');\n  const flightCountEl = dom('flightCount');\n\n  const cwndVal = dom('cwndVal');\n  const ssthVal = dom('ssthVal');\n  const stateVal = dom('stateVal');\n  const rttVal = dom('rttVal');\n  const thrVal = dom('thrVal');\n\n  const logArea = dom('log');\n  const plot = dom('plot');\n  const ctx = plot.getContext('2d');\n\n  const aimdParams = dom('aimdParams');\n  const cubicParams = dom('cubicParams');\n  const bbrParams = dom('bbrParams');\n\n  // Show/hide parameter panels\n  function updateParamPanels(){\n    const a = algoEl.value;\n    aimdParams.style.display = (a==='aimd'?'block':'none');\n    cubicParams.style.display = (a==='cubic'?'block':'none');\n    bbrParams.style.display = (a==='bbr'?'block':'none');\n  }\n  algoEl.addEventListener('change', updateParamPanels);\n  updateParamPanels();\n\n  // Simulation object\n  const sim = {\n    running:false,\n    timer:null,\n    stepIntervalMs:20,\n    timeMs:0,\n    nextSeq:1,\n    events:[], // scheduled manual events\n    packets:[], // all packets (sent or scheduled)\n    inFlight:[], // packets not yet acked\n    delivered:[], // history of delivered packets\n    cwnd:2, ssth:1000, state:'SlowStart', // sender state\n    dupacks:{}, // map seq->dup ack count\n    lastAcked:0,\n    losses:0,\n    rttBase:80,\n    rttCurrent:80,\n    bandwidthMbps:10,\n    queueMax:100,\n    queue:[], // queued packets waiting for transmission\n    linkUp:true,\n    logLines:[],\n    plotSamples:[], // {t,cwnd,throughput,rtt,queueSize}\n    lastRecordedMs:0,\n    packetSize:1460,\n    mss:1460,\n    lastLossTime:0,\n    cubicState:{wMax:0, tLastLoss:0}, // for cubic\n    bbrState:{bwEst:0, rttMin:Infinity, lastProbe:0},\n    configVersion:1\n  };\n\n  // Logging\n  function log(s){\n    const line = '['+formatMs(sim.timeMs)+'] '+s;\n    sim.logLines.push(line);\n    if (showLog.checked) {\n      logArea.value = sim.logLines.join('\\\\n');\n      logArea.scrollTop = logArea.scrollHeight;\n    }\n  }\n\n  function clearLog(){\n    sim.logLines = []; logArea.value=''; \n  }\n  clearLogBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){ clearLog(); });\n\n  exportLogBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    const blob = new Blob([sim.logLines.join('\\\\n')],'text/plain');\n    const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);\n    const a = document.createElement('a');\n    a.href = url; a.download = 'sim_log.txt'; a.click();\n    URL.revokeObjectURL(url);\n  });\n\n  // Format helpers\n  function formatMs(ms){ return (ms/1000).toFixed(3)+'s'; }\n  function formatMbps(x){ return x.toFixed(2); }\n\n  // Initialize / reset\n  function resetSim(){\n    stop();\n    sim.timeMs = 0;\n    sim.nextSeq = 1;\n    sim.events = [];\n    sim.packets = [];\n    sim.inFlight = [];\n    sim.delivered = [];\n    sim.cwnd = Math.max(1, Number(initCWND.value));\n    sim.ssth = Math.max(1, Number(initSSTH.value));\n    sim.state = 'SlowStart';\n    sim.dupacks = {};\n    sim.lastAcked = 0;\n    sim.losses = 0;\n    sim.rttBase = Number(rttEl.value);\n    sim.rttCurrent = sim.rttBase;\n    sim.bandwidthMbps = Number(bandwidthEl.value);\n    sim.queueMax = Number(queueEl.value);\n    sim.queue = [];\n    sim.linkUp = true;\n    sim.logLines = [];\n    sim.plotSamples = [];\n    sim.lastRecordedMs = 0;\n    sim.packetSize = Number(mssEl.value);\n    sim.mss = sim.packetSize;\n    sim.lastLossTime = 0;\n    sim.cubicState = {wMax:sim.cwnd, tLastLoss:0};\n    sim.bbrState = {bwEst:sim.bandwidthMbps, rttMin:sim.rttBase, lastProbe:0};\n    quickLog('Reset simulation');\n    updateDisplay();\n    drawPlot();\n  }\n\n  function quickLog(s){\n    // short logs for immediate feedback\n    log(s);\n  }\n\n  resetBtn.addEventListener('click', resetSim);\n\n  // Play/Stop\n  function start(){\n    if(sim.running) return;\n    sim.running = true;\n    playBtn.textContent = 'Pause';\n    sim.stepIntervalMs = Math.max(1, Math.floor(1000/Number(speedEl.value)));\n    runLoop();\n  }\n\n  function stop(){\n    sim.running = false;\n    playBtn.textContent = 'Play';\n    if(sim.timer){ clearTimeout(sim.timer); sim.timer = null; }\n  }\n\n  playBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    if(sim.running) stop(); else start();\n  });\n\n  // Step\n  stepBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    tick();\n  });\n\n  fastRunBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    for(let i=0;i<500;i++) tick();\n  });\n\n  // Link down\n  linkDownBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    let duration = Number(linkDownFor.value);\n    if(duration<=0) { quickLog('Specify positive ms for link down'); return; }\n    sim.linkUp = false;\n    quickLog('Link down for '+duration+' ms');\n    setTimeout(function(){\n      sim.linkUp = true;\n      quickLog('Link resumed');\n    }, duration);\n  });\n\n  // Set cross-traffic\n  setXBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    const v = Number(setX.value);\n    xtrafficEl.value = v;\n    quickLog('Set cross-traffic to '+v+' Mbps');\n  });\n\n  // Manual drop\n  dropBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    const seq = Number(dropSeqEl.value);\n    if(!seq){ quickLog('Enter seq to drop'); return; }\n    // find packet\n    const p = sim.packets.find(x=>x.seq===seq && !x.dropped && !x.acked);\n    if(!p){ quickLog('Packet not found or already handled'); return; }\n    p.dropped = true;\n    sim.losses++;\n    sim.lastLossTime = sim.timeMs;\n    quickLog('Manually dropped packet seq '+seq);\n    handleLossEvent(p);\n  });\n\n  // Delay packet\n  delayBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    const seq = Number(delaySeqEl.value);\n    const ms = Number(delayMsEl.value);\n    if(!seq || !ms){ quickLog('Enter seq and ms'); return; }\n    const p = sim.packets.find(x=>x.seq===seq && !x.acked && !x.dropped);\n    if(!p){ quickLog('Packet not found for delay'); return; }\n    p.extraDelay = (p.extraDelay||0) + ms;\n    quickLog('Delayed packet '+seq+' by '+ms+' ms');\n  });\n\n  // Inspect packet\n  inspectBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    const seq = Number(inspectSeq.value);\n    if(!seq){ quickLog('Enter seq to inspect'); return; }\n    const p = sim.packets.find(x=>x.seq===seq);\n    if(!p){ quickLog('No record of seq '+seq); return; }\n    quickLog('Packet '+seq+': sentAt='+formatMs(p.sentAt)+', delivered='+!!p.delivered+', dropped='+!!p.dropped+', acked='+!!p.acked+', extraDelay='+ (p.extraDelay||0));\n  });\n\n  // Save/load scenario\n  saveBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    const scenario = {\n      algo: algoEl.value,\n      initCWND: initCWND.value,\n      initSSTH: initSSTH.value,\n      mss: mssEl.value,\n      dupThresh: dupThreshEl.value,\n      ai: aiEl.value,\n      beta: betaEl.value,\n      cubicC: cubicC.value,\n      tcpFriend: tcpFriend.value,\n      bbrGain: bbrGain.value,\n      bbrInterval: bbrInterval.value,\n      rtt: rttEl.value,\n      bandwidth: bandwidthEl.value,\n      queue: queueEl.value,\n      xtraffic: xtrafficEl.value,\n      lossModel: lossModelEl.value,\n      lossProb: lossProbEl.value,\n      mode: modeEl.value,\n      tickMs: tickMsEl.value\n    };\n    scenarioJson.value = JSON.stringify(scenario, null, 2);\n    quickLog('Scenario saved to text area');\n  });\n\n  loadBtn.addEventListener('click', function(){\n    try{\n      const sc = JSON.parse(scenarioJson.value);\n      algoEl.value = sc.algo || algoEl.value;\n      initCWND.value = sc.initCWND || initCWND.value;\n      initSSTH.value = sc.initSSTH || initSSTH.value;\n      mssEl.value = sc.mss || mssEl.value;\n      dupThreshEl.value = sc.dupThresh || dupThreshEl.value;\n      aiEl.value = sc.ai || aiEl.value;\n      betaEl.value = sc.beta || betaEl.value;\n      cubicC.value = sc.cubicC || cubicC.value;\n      tcpFriend.value = sc.tcpFriend || tcpFriend.value;\n      bbrGain.value = sc.bbrGain || bbrGain.value;\n      bbrInterval.value = sc.bbrInterval || bbrInterval.value;\n      rttEl.value = sc.rtt || rttEl.value;\n      bandwidthEl.value = sc.bandwidth || bandwidthEl.value;\n      queueEl.value = sc.queue || queueEl.value;\n      xtrafficEl.value = sc.xtraffic || xtrafficEl.value;\n      lossModelEl.value = sc.lossModel || lossModelEl.value;\n      lossProbEl.value = sc.lossProb || lossProbEl.value;\n      modeEl.value = sc.mode || modeEl.value;\n      tickMsEl.value = sc.tickMs || tickMsEl.value;\n      updateParamPanels();\n      quickLog('Scenario loaded');\n      resetSim();\n    }catch(e){ quickLog('Invalid JSON scenario'); }\n  });\n\n  // Update displays\n  function updateDisplay(){\n    cwndVal.textContent = sim.cwnd.toFixed(3);\n    ssthVal.textContent = sim.ssth.toFixed(1);\n    stateVal.textContent = sim.state;\n    rttVal.textContent = sim.rttCurrent.toFixed(1);\n    // throughput estimate: last second delivered bytes\n    const lastSec = sim.delivered.filter(p=>p.deliveredAt && (sim.timeMs - p.deliveredAt)<=1000);\n    const bytes = lastSec.reduce((a,p)=>a + p.size,0);\n    const mbps = bytes*8/1000/1000;\n    thrVal.textContent = mbps.toFixed(3);\n    simTimeEl.value = (sim.timeMs/1000).toFixed(3);\n    schedCountEl.value = sim.events.length;\n    flightCountEl.value = sim.inFlight.length;\n  }\n\n  // Plotting\n  function drawPlot(){\n    // Clear\n    ctx.clearRect(0,0,plot.width,plot.height);\n    // axes: time horizontal, cwnd vertical\n    const samples = sim.plotSamples;\n    if(samples.length<2) return;\n    const maxT = samples[samples.length-1].t;\n    const minT = Math.max(0, maxT - 30*1000); // show last 30s\n    const vis = samples.filter(s=>s.t>=minT);\n    if(vis.length<2) return;\n    const cwnds = vis.map(v=>v.cwnd);\n    const maxC = Math.max(1, Math.max(...cwnds));\n    // draw cwnd\n    ctx.beginPath();\n    for(let i=0;i<vis.length;i++){\n      const v = vis[i];\n      const x = ((v.t-minT)/(maxT-minT)) * plot.width;\n      const y = plot.height - (v.cwnd/maxC) * plot.height;\n      if(i===0) ctx.moveTo(x,y); else ctx.lineTo(x,y);\n    }\n    ctx.strokeStyle = '#000';\n    ctx.lineWidth = 1;\n    ctx.stroke();\n    // small ticks and labels (text)\n    ctx.fillStyle = '#000';\n    ctx.font = '10px monospace';\n    ctx.fillText('cwnd (pkts) over last '+((maxT-minT)/1000).toFixed(0)+'s', 6, 12);\n    ctx.fillText('max cwnd '+maxC.toFixed(1), 6, 24);\n  }\n\n  // Core packet sending logic\n  function sendPackets(){\n    // sender can send up to cwnd - inFlight\n    const inFlightCount = sim.inFlight.length;\n    const allowed = Math.floor(sim.cwnd) - inFlightCount;\n    if(allowed<=0) return;\n    for(let i=0;i<allowed;i++){\n      const seq = sim.nextSeq++;\n      const p = {\n        seq: seq,\n        size: sim.mss,\n        sentAt: sim.timeMs,\n        delivered:false,\n        dropped:false,\n        acked:false,\n        extraDelay:0\n      };\n      sim.packets.push(p);\n      sim.inFlight.push(p);\n      // place into queue (model)\n      enqueuePacket(p);\n      log('Sent packet seq '+seq+' cwnd='+sim.cwnd.toFixed(2));\n    }\n  }\n\n  function enqueuePacket(p){\n    // combined arrival: if link down or queue overflow or random loss may drop immediately.\n    // Queue is simple FIFO with finite buffer.\n    // When enqueued, it will be popped/transmitted by linkProcess\n    if(!sim.linkUp){\n      // link down: packet stalls; mark as queued and will wait until link up\n      sim.queue.push(p);\n      return;\n    }\n    // Random loss model\n    if(lossModelEl.value==='random'){\n      const prob = Number(lossProbEl.value);\n      if(Math.random()<prob){\n        p.dropped = true;\n        p.dropReason = 'random';\n        sim.losses++;\n        sim.lastLossTime = sim.timeMs;\n        handleLossEvent(p);\n        return;\n      }\n    }\n    // If queue full -> drop tail\n    if(sim.queue.length >= sim.queueMax){\n      const dropNew = true; // tail drop\n      if(dropNew){\n        p.dropped = true;\n        p.dropReason = 'queue';\n        sim.losses++;\n        sim.lastLossTime = sim.timeMs;\n        handleLossEvent(p);\n        return;\n      } else {\n        const old = sim.queue.shift();\n        old.dropped = true;\n        old.dropReason='queue';\n        sim.losses++;\n        handleLossEvent(old);\n        sim.queue.push(p);\n        return;\n      }\n    }\n    sim.queue.push(p);\n  }\n\n  // Link processing: transmit bytes according to bandwidth and cross traffic\n  function linkProcess(dtMs){\n    if(!sim.linkUp) return;\n    // available bandwidth in bytes for this tick\n    const totalBw = Math.max(0, sim.bandwidthMbps - Number(xtrafficEl.value));\n    const bwBytesPerSec = totalBw * 1000 * 1000 / 8;\n    const allowedBytes = bwBytesPerSec * (dtMs/1000);\n    // send as many queued packets as allowed\n    let budget = allowedBytes;\n    while(sim.queue.length>0 && budget > 0){\n      const p = sim.queue[0];\n      const b = p.size;\n      if(budget >= b){\n        // transmit this packet\n        sim.queue.shift();\n        budget -= b;\n        // schedule delivery after propagation (half RTT) plus queueing as model\n        const prop = (sim.rttBase/2);\n        const qDelay = 0; // queue added in this model already via queueing\n        const extra = p.extraDelay || 0;\n        const deliverTime = sim.timeMs + prop + qDelay + extra;\n        setTimeout(()=>{ // use real-time scheduling only to mimic extraDelay; but actual state will be updated in tick checks\n          // nothing - delivery will be processed by pollDeliveries in tick loop via sim.packets list using deliveredAt\n        },0);\n        // mark delivered when sim.timeMs passes deliverTime\n        p.deliverAt = deliverTime;\n      } else {\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Poll for deliveries and ACKs\n  function pollDeliveries(){\n    // any packet with deliverAt <= current time and not yet delivered and not dropped -> mark delivered and generate ACK later (RTT/2)\n    sim.packets.forEach(p=>{\n      if(!p.delivered && !p.dropped && p.deliverAt !== undefined && p.deliverAt <= sim.timeMs){\n        p.delivered = true;\n        p.deliveredAt = sim.timeMs;\n        // schedule ACK arriving at sender after remaining half-RTT\n        const ackTime = sim.timeMs + (sim.rttBase/2); // simple\n        p.ackAt = ackTime;\n        sim.delivered.push(p);\n      }\n      if(p.delivered && !p.acked && p.ackAt !== undefined && p.ackAt <= sim.timeMs){\n        // process ACK\n        p.acked = true;\n        p.ackReceivedAt = sim.timeMs;\n        processAck(p);\n      }\n      // dropped packets are processed for sender recognition by dupacks/timeouts\n      if(p.dropped && !p.dropNoted){\n        // mark drop noted; simulate that it will never be delivered; sender will detect via dup-acks/timeouts\n        p.dropNoted = true;\n      }\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Process ack at sender\n  function processAck(p){\n    // If ack seq is > lastAcked, update lastAcked and update cwnd based on algorithm\n    if(p.seq <= sim.lastAcked){\n      // duplicate ack\n      sim.dupacks[p.seq] = (sim.dupacks[p.seq]||0) + 1;\n      if(sim.dupacks[p.seq] >= Number(dupThreshEl.value)){\n        // fast retransmit\n        if(!p.fastRetransmitted){\n          sim.losses++;\n          sim.lastLossTime = sim.timeMs;\n          quickLog('Fast retransmit triggered by dupACKs on seq '+p.seq);\n          p.fastRetransmitted = true;\n          handleLossEvent(p);\n        }\n      }\n      return;\n    }\n    // new ack\n    sim.lastAcked = p.seq;\n    // remove from inFlight\n    sim.inFlight = sim.inFlight.filter(ip => ip.seq > p.seq);\n    // reset dupacks for lower seqs\n    Object.keys(sim.dupacks).forEach(k=>{\n      if(Number(k) <= p.seq) delete sim.dupacks[k];\n    });\n\n    // Update RTT estimate and BBR state\n    sim.rttCurrent = Math.max(sim.rttBase, sim.rttBase + sim.queue.length * (sim.mss/(sim.bandwidthMbps*1000000/8) * 1000));\n    if(sim.rttCurrent < sim.bbrState.rttMin) sim.bbrState.rttMin = sim.rttCurrent;\n\n    // Algorithm-specific cwnd update\n    const algo = algoEl.value;\n    if(algo === 'reno'){\n      if(sim.state === 'SlowStart'){\n        sim.cwnd += 1; // +MSS per ACK roughly; normalized to packets\n        if(sim.cwnd >= sim.ssth){\n          sim.state = 'CongAvoid';\n        }\n      } else if(sim.state === 'CongAvoid'){\n        // additive increase per RTT ~ +1 per RTT. We increment per ACK by 1/cwnd\n        sim.cwnd += 1 / Math.max(1, sim.cwnd);\n      } else if(sim.state === 'FastRecovery'){\n        // in fast recovery cwnd behavior simplified: set cwnd to ssth and then exit on new ack\n        sim.state = 'CongAvoid';\n      }\n    } else if(algo === 'aimd'){\n      if(sim.cwnd < sim.ssth){\n        // keep additive increase similar to slow start or treat as AIMD increases slowly\n        sim.cwnd += Number(aiEl.value);\n      } else {\n        sim.cwnd += Number(aiEl.value) / Math.max(1, sim.cwnd);\n      }\n    } else if(algo === 'cubic'){\n      // simplified cubic: cwnd evolves based on time since last loss\n      const C = Number(cubicC.value);\n      const t = (sim.timeMs - sim.cubicState.tLastLoss)/1000;\n      const K = Math.cbrt(sim.cubicState.wMax*(1-Number(tcpFriend.value))/C + 0.000001) || 0;\n      const Wt = C*Math.pow(t-K,3) + sim.cubicState.wMax;\n      const tcpFair = sim.cubicState.wMax * Number(tcpFriend.value) + (3*(1-Number(tcpFriend.value))/ (1 + sim.cwnd));\n      sim.cwnd = Math.max(1, Math.max(Wt, tcpFair));\n    } else if(algo === 'bbr'){\n      // estimate bw and set cwnd = bw * rtt * gain\n      // estimate bw using delivered bytes over last 1s\n      const lastSec = sim.delivered.filter(pp=>pp.deliveredAt && (sim.timeMs - pp.deliveredAt)<=1000);\n      const bytes = lastSec.reduce((a,p)=>a + p.size,0);\n      const bwEst = bytes*8/1000/1000; // Mbps\n      if(bwEst>0) sim.bbrState.bwEst = 0.7*sim.bbrState.bwEst + 0.3*bwEst;\n      const gain = Number(bbrGain.value);\n      const rttSec = sim.rttCurrent/1000;\n      sim.cwnd = Math.max(1, (sim.bbrState.bwEst * 1000 * 1000 / 8) * rttSec / sim.mss * gain);\n    }\n\n    // ensure cwnd bounds\n    sim.cwnd = clamp(sim.cwnd, 0.5, 100000);\n\n    quickLog('ACK for seq '+p.seq+' cwnd now '+sim.cwnd.toFixed(3));\n  }\n\n  // Loss handling\n  function handleLossEvent(p){\n    // On loss, adjust cwnd and ssth based on algo\n    const algo = algoEl.value;\n    if(algo === 'reno'){\n      sim.ssth = Math.max(2, sim.cwnd / 2);\n      sim.cwnd = Math.max(1, sim.ssth);\n      sim.state = 'SlowStart';\n    } else if(algo === 'aimd'){\n      const beta = Number(betaEl.value);\n      sim.ssth = Math.max(2, sim.cwnd * beta);\n      sim.cwnd = Math.max(1, sim.cwnd * beta);\n      sim.state = 'CongAvoid';\n    } else if(algo === 'cubic'){\n      // record wMax and reduce cwnd\n      sim.cubicState.wMax = sim.cwnd;\n      sim.cubicState.tLastLoss = sim.timeMs;\n      sim.cwnd = Math.max(1, sim.cwnd * 0.7);\n      sim.ssth = Math.max(2, sim.cwnd);\n      sim.state = 'CongAvoid';\n      quickLog('CUBIC: loss at seq '+p.seq+' wMax set to '+sim.cubicState.wMax.toFixed(2));\n    } else if(algo === 'bbr'){\n      // BBR reduces pacing/gain; simplified: reduce cwnd to estimate bw*rtt\n      sim.bbrState.bwEst = Math.max(0.1, sim.bbrState.bwEst * 0.9);\n      sim.cwnd = Math.max(1, (sim.bbrState.bwEst * 1000 * 1000 / 8) * (sim.bbrState.rttMin/1000) * Number(bbrGain.value) );\n      sim.state = 'ProbeBW';\n    }\n    // Mark dropped packet as acked to remove from inFlight for this simulator; the sender will eventually retransmit but we do simplified behavior\n    sim.inFlight = sim.inFlight.filter(ip => ip.seq !== p.seq);\n    log('Loss detected seq '+p.seq+'; cwnd->'+sim.cwnd.toFixed(2)+', ssth->'+sim.ssth.toFixed(1));\n  }\n\n  // Engine tick\n  function tick(){\n    // update parameters live\n    sim.rttBase = Number(rttEl.value);\n    sim.bandwidthMbps = Number(bandwidthEl.value);\n    sim.queueMax = Number(queueEl.value);\n    sim.mss = Number(mssEl.value);\n\n    // time advance\n    const dt = Number(tickMsEl.value);\n    sim.timeMs += dt;\n\n    // send new packets according to cwnd\n    if(modeEl.value === 'packet'){\n      sendPackets();\n      linkProcess(dt);\n      pollDeliveries();\n    } else {\n      // RTT aggregated mode: operate in coarse steps: per RTT, try to send cwnd packets and process losses probabilistically\n      // If dt accumulates to >= RTT, do an RTT-round update\n      if(!sim._aggAcc) sim._aggAcc = 0;\n      sim._aggAcc += dt;\n      if(sim._aggAcc >= sim.rttBase){\n        sim._aggAcc = 0;\n        // send cwnd packets\n        const toSend = Math.max(1, Math.floor(sim.cwnd));\n        for(let i=0;i<toSend;i++){\n          const seq=sim.nextSeq++;\n          const p = {seq, size:sim.mss, sentAt:sim.timeMs, delivered:false, dropped:false, acked:false};\n          sim.packets.push(p);\n          sim.inFlight.push(p);\n          // determine loss: random or queue overflow\n          let drop=false;\n          if(lossModelEl.value==='random'){\n            if(Math.random() < Number(lossProbEl.value)){\n              drop=true;\n            }\n          }\n          // queue overflow: if toSend > queueMax -> drop fraction\n          if(sim.queueMax < toSend && Math.random() < 0.2) drop=true;\n          if(drop){\n            p.dropped=true;\n            sim.losses++;\n            handleLossEvent(p);\n            continue;\n          } else {\n            // ACK this RTT\n            p.delivered=true; p.deliveredAt = sim.timeMs;\n            p.ackAt = sim.timeMs + sim.rttBase/2;\n            // immediate ack processing\n            processAck(p);\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Recording for plot every recordInt\n    if(sim.timeMs - sim.lastRecordedMs >= Number(recordInt.value)){\n      sim.lastRecordedMs = sim.timeMs;\n      sim.plotSamples.push({t:sim.timeMs, cwnd:sim.cwnd, throughput:0, rtt:sim.rttCurrent, queueSize:sim.queue.length});\n      if(sim.plotSamples.length>2000) sim.plotSamples.shift();\n      drawPlot();\n    }\n\n    // auto stop on loss count\n    const stopAt = Number(autoStopLoss.value);\n    if(stopAt>0 && sim.losses>=stopAt){\n      stop();\n      quickLog('Auto-stopped due to losses >= '+stopAt);\n    }\n\n    updateDisplay();\n  }\n\n  // main loop for running\n  function runLoop(){\n    if(!sim.running) return;\n    tick();\n    // schedule next\n    sim.timer = setTimeout(runLoop, sim.stepIntervalMs);\n  }\n\n  // initial reset\n  resetSim();\n\n  // update param panels initial\n  updateParamPanels();\n\n  // external debug helpers\n  window.__sim = sim;\n\n  // periodically redraw plot in case of changes\n  setInterval(function(){ drawPlot(); updateDisplay(); }, 500);\n\n  // Manual controls wiring done above\n\n  // Additional exploration actions: allow user to schedule events (not UI heavy)\n  // For example: event queue for scriptable changes\n  // Provide basic scheduling via console API: __simSchedule({t:+1000, action: function(sim){ ... }})\n  window.__simSchedule = function(ev){\n    // ev: {delayMs:1000, action: function}\n    const due = sim.timeMs + (ev.delayMs||0);\n    sim.events.push({due:due, action:ev.action, raw:ev});\n    sim.events.sort((a,b)=>a.due-b.due);\n    schedCountEl.value = sim.events.length;\n  };\n\n  // background event runner: process scheduled events in tick\n  setInterval(function(){\n    if(sim.events.length===0) return;\n    const now = sim.timeMs;\n    while(sim.events.length && sim.events[0].due <= now){\n      const e = sim.events.shift();\n      try{ e.action(sim); quickLog('Ran scheduled event'); }catch(err){ quickLog('Event error: '+err); }\n    }\n    schedCountEl.value = sim.events.length;\n  }, 50);\n\n  // Expose quick controls for interactive sequences\n  // For user's ability to explore deep interactions:\n  // - switch algorithms during run: user can change algo dropdown anytime\n  // - change bandwidth/rtt/queue on the fly\n  // - manual drops/delays\n  // - scheduling via __simSchedule from console\n  quickLog('Simulator ready. Use controls above to explore congestion control behaviors.');\n})();\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
